From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 23:35:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/nouveau/nv50: invalidate PFIFO TLB for channel VMM
 updates

PFIFO reads GPFIFO entries and indirect push buffers through the channel
VMM.  However, channel creation does not account for PFIFO in
vmm->engref.  Consequently, nv50_vmm_flush() does not invalidate engine
0x05 when mappings in a channel VMM change.

The older nv50 VM implementation invoked pfifo->tlb_flush() for channel
VMs.  The engine-module conversion dropped that engine-0x05 flush while
switching VM invalidation to registered engine users and callbacks.
Current channel construction does not account for PFIFO in engref either.
The missing invalidation can leave PFIFO fetching commands through a stale
translation, producing DMA_PUSHER INVALID_CMD/INVALID_MTHD faults followed
by unrelated graphics engine faults.

Track PFIFO as a VMM user for the lifetime of every hardware channel and
map NVKM_ENGINE_FIFO to Tesla's engine-0x05 TLB invalidate.

Fixes: ebb945a94bba ("drm/nouveau: port all engines to new engine module format")
Link: https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/linux/+bug/2128858
Link: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/nouveau/-/issues/480
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/engine/fifo/chan.c    | 2 ++
 drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/mmu/vmmnv50.c | 1 +
 2 files changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/engine/fifo/chan.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/engine/fifo/chan.c
index 3b25205118b0..6a419942f8b0 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/engine/fifo/chan.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/engine/fifo/chan.c
@@ -282,6 +282,7 @@ nvkm_chan_del(struct nvkm_chan **pchan)
 	nvkm_memory_unref(&chan->userd.mem);
 
 	if (chan->vmm) {
+		atomic_dec(&chan->vmm->engref[NVKM_ENGINE_FIFO]);
 		nvkm_vmm_part(chan->vmm, chan->inst->memory);
 		nvkm_vmm_unref(&chan->vmm);
 	}
@@ -425,6 +426,7 @@ nvkm_chan_new_(const struct nvkm_chan_func *func, struct nvkm_runl *runl, int ru
 		}
 
 		chan->vmm = nvkm_vmm_ref(vmm);
+		atomic_inc(&chan->vmm->engref[NVKM_ENGINE_FIFO]);
 	}
 
 	/* Allocate HW ctxdma for push buffer. */
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/mmu/vmmnv50.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/mmu/vmmnv50.c
index 4c2a05d456af..4edf08087d2f 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/mmu/vmmnv50.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/nouveau/nvkm/subdev/mmu/vmmnv50.c
@@ -200,5 +200,6 @@ nv50_vmm_flush(struct nvkm_vmm *vmm, int level)
 		case NVKM_ENGINE_VP    :
 		case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPDEC: id = 0x01; break;
+		case NVKM_ENGINE_FIFO  : id = 0x05; break;
 		case NVKM_SUBDEV_BAR   : id = 0x06; break;
 		case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPPP :
 		case NVKM_ENGINE_MPEG  : id = 0x08; break;
-- 
